117
00:06:33,946 --> 00:06:38,071
Now, let me just show you two ways
to share some of your results.

118
00:06:38,794 --> 00:06:41,494
First, SWOT analysis.

119
00:06:41,661 --> 00:06:45,223
With the SWOT analysis you
systematically analyze the strengths

120
00:06:45,648 --> 00:06:49,873
weaknesses, opportunities,
and threats, for the implementation

121
00:06:50,028 --> 00:06:52,253
of a proper fecal sludge
management scheme

122
00:06:52,407 --> 00:06:53,920
in your city.

123
00:06:54,185 --> 00:06:57,822
Strengths and weaknesses describe
existing situations whereas

124
00:06:57,982 --> 00:07:00,607
opportunities and threats
represent the potential

125
00:07:00,771 --> 00:07:02,534
that you've identified.

126
00:07:02,688 --> 00:07:06,363
You can make this assessment more
systematic by doing it for each

127
00:07:06,515 --> 00:07:09,515
of the enabling
environment components.

128
00:07:09,799 --> 00:07:13,837
Secondly, you were already
introduced to the Shit Flow Diagrams

129
00:07:14,005 --> 00:07:15,805
or SFDs.

